Early Access Review

Man this game is awesome, I mean, the game have two months and have so much stuff in it.
Of course, this is an Alpha Version game, and of course that have its bugs but it is really playable.

Pros:
- Third Person View (for me it's a pro, cause there is some survival games there don't have it);
- Full functional Base Building System;
- Real Life Human Body Reactions due to the biomes (starvation, hot, cold, the clothes influence the body temperature, etç..);
- Crafting System 100% Working (if you mouse over each item you'll see hints for how to make it, and you have a Hurtworld Wiki to help you more);

Cons:
- The Weather System is working but I don't really like it. It's a bit buggy (some times you are hearing the rain sound and then no water is falling from the sky);
- The game is too cartoonished, I mean I like the concept but I think it is a bit too much;
- As I said before the Base Building System is full functional, but it have to have more stuff" to construct

Early Access Review

I love when people list their pros and cons, it seems to give a balanced perepective of the game, then you realise it's all  subjective anyway so pick the bones out of this;

You will spawn slightly bewildered and immediate seek to arm yourself in an arid sparse landscape, naked assassins await so make that flint hatchet quickly! Scour the valleys around you for resources to craft better equipment, clothes and weapons rambo'ing all that dare challenge you (or run away to safety, your call). Build a simple house and stake your claim to your bit of land before planning out your next excursion for the resources to make better gear you will need to survive for longer and longer. Farm animals and fruit to keep from starving, heat your weathered bones with campfires, firepits and eventually even a blast furnace. Explore a surpirsingly big map with diverse biomes each holding new challenges from extreme desert to freezing snow valleys. Find abandoned towns and loot for rare items whilst always keeping an eye out for others, those pesky others. Build up your base and add traps, drilling equipment and more to make harvesting the best resources a little easier, then go out geared up to destroy all who cross you only to be bonked on the head by a sneaky naked with a flint hatchet!

Early Access Review

I must say, first of all, that this is the best and most polished alpha I must have played. The game lacks some features but it is far from empty and there is more content available than in many betas. And, most importantly, the features that are implemented do actually work correctly must of the time (the occasional glitch or bug does happen).

Pros:
Cartoonesque graphics do look awesome and do not punish performance;
Running people over is fun;
Simplistic crafting and building system (make complex structures with simple tools);
A decent amount of community servers and official servers;


Cons:
Too easy to get into an end-game state (get a car early and call it a good game);
Still no decent weapon recoil;

I highly recommend it.
